President Cyril Ramaphosa Ramaphosa announced an ease in the level of regulations of the national lockdown. Ramaphosa addressed the nation on Thursday evening, said the lockdown has managed to slow down the spread of the coronavirus. He additionally announced an ease in the level of regulations of the national lockdown to level 4 will start on May 1. The national lockdown alert level 4 means that South Africans will be able to buy cigarettes, but the sale of alcohol is still prohibited. He further said that some sectors will be allowed to go back to operation, however where possible workers that are able to work from home should be allowed to do so. Ramaphosa added that in some cases, a sector will not be able to return to full production during Level 4 while the risk of infection remains high.   